<html>  <head>    <meta content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" http-equiv="content-type">    <title>Bible API Aggregate Service</title>    <style type="text/css">.code {    font-family: "Lucida Console", Monaco, monospace;    font-size: small;}.ind {    margin-left: 40px;}#header {    background-image: url("images/bible.png");}#title {  text-shadow: 2px 2px 0px white;    color: #663366;    font-variant: small-caps;}body {    width: 700px;    font-family: Calibri, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;}h2 {    color: #663366;}h1 {  text-shadow: 2px 2px 0px #999999;}</style></head>  <body>    <h1 id="title"></h1>    <table style="width: 700px; height: 67px;" border="0">      <tbody>        <tr>          <td id="header">            <h1 id="title">Bible API Aggregate Web Service</h1>          </td>        </tr>      </tbody>    </table>    The Bible API Aggregate Web Service brings together a number of Bible APIs    on the web to offer a comprehensive set of Bibles to quote from. This    service offers two REST-based APIs: <a href="#getVersions">getVersions</a>    and <a href="#getQuote">getQuote</a>.<br>    <h2> <a name="getVersions"></a>getVersions</h2>    <p>Lists all supported Bible versions. </p>    <h3>Format</h3>    <p class="ind"><a class="code" href="http://service/getVersions" title="http://service/getVersions">http://service/getVersions</a></p>    <h3> Returns</h3>    This returns a JSON object of key/value pairs. The <em>keys</em> are the    keys that can be used as the Bible version parameter in the getQuote service    and the <em>values</em> are objects with title, description, and copyright    entries in plain text. <br>    <p> Example:</p>    <div class="code ind"> { <br>      <div class="code ind">asv: { <br>        <div class="code ind"> id: "asv",<br>          title : "American Standard Version", <br>          copyright : "Public Domain", <br>          description : "The ASV has long been regarded by many scholars..." </div>        }, ... </div>      } </div>    <p>The following Bibles are currently available: </p>    <% for (var i in bibles) { %>    	<div class="ind"><b>Key:</b> <%= bibles[i].id %></div>   		<div class="ind"><b>Title:</b> <%= bibles[i].title %></div>   		<div class="ind"><b>Description:</b> <%= bibles[i].description %></div> 		<div class="ind"><b>Copyright:</b> <%= bibles[i].copyright %></div>   		<br>	<% } %>    <h2><a name="getQuote"></a>getQuote</h2>    <p>Look up a book/chapter/verse in a particular Bible version.&nbsp;</p>    <h3>Format</h3>    <p class="code ind">http://service/getQuote/?version=&lt;version&gt;&amp;book=&lt;book&gt;&amp;chapter=&lt;chapter&gt;&amp;verse=&lt;verse&gt;</p>    <p class="ind"></p>    <table style="border=" 0"="" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="1">      <tbody>      </tbody>      <thead>        <tr style="background-color: silver;">          <td><strong>Parameter</strong></td>          <td><strong>Type</strong></td>          <td><strong>Description</strong></td>        </tr>      </thead>      <tbody>        <tr>          <td>version</td>          <td><em>string</em></td>          <td>One of the keys listed in the <a href="#getVersions">getVersions</a>            call.</td>        </tr>        <tr>          <td>book</td>          <td><em>string</em></td>          <td>One of the books of the bible.</td>        </tr>        <tr>          <td>chapter</td>          <td><em>number</em></td>          <td>A chapter within the book.</td>        </tr>        <tr>          <td>verse</td>          <td><em>number</em> or <em>range</em></td>          <td>Number or range of numbers within the chapter. A range is            signified by a number followed by minus sign and then another            number.</td>        </tr>      </tbody>    </table>    <p>Example:</p>    <p class="code ind">http://service/getQuote/?version=esv&amp;book=John&amp;chapter=3&amp;verse=16</p>    <h3>Returns</h3>    <p>A JSON object with the version, book, chapter, verse, and associated      passage.</p>    <p>Example:</p>    <div class="code ind">{      <div class="code ind">version: 'esv',<br>        book: 'John',<br>        chapter: 3, <br>        verse: 16, <br>        passage: "\"For God so loved the world, that he gave his only Son, that        whoever believes in him should not perish but have eternal life."" </div>      }</div>    <h2>Credits</h2>    <p>Many thanks to the following services: <a href="http://api.biblia.com/docs/">Biblia.com</a>,      <a href="http://bibles.org/pages/api">Bible Search</a>, <a href="http://www.esvapi.org/api">ESV
        Bible Web Service</a>, and <a href="https://labs.bible.org/api_web_service">Bible.org</a></p>  </body></html>